[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care-coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-source care-plan-of-record integration as architectural primitive.** The synthesized view is a first-class data product, with named ownership at the engineering-plus-clinical-operations team, with defined source-of-truth boundaries, defined conflict-resolution rules, defined update cadences per source, and per-source data-quality monitoring.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-bot orchestration as first-class architecture.** The care-coordination assistant is the orchestrator-level bot for high-touch patients across the chapter 11 surface. The orchestration includes context handoff to specialist bots, return-from-specialist-bot handling, and conversation-thread continuity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Program-specific protocol delivery with per-program governance.** Each program (oncology, perinatal, post-discharge, etc.) has a defined protocol library reviewed and signed off by the program's clinical and care-management leadership. The bot delivers from the protocol; the bot does not freestyle.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-manager-workforce integration as primary architectural component.** The bot is deployed alongside an active care-management workforce. The named-care-manager relationship is preserved. Warm handoffs route to the named manager with full context. Workforce capacity is sized so the bot extends the manager's reach.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **SDOH-screening-and-resource-navigation as architectural primitive.** SDOH screening and resource navigation are first-class capabilities, not add-ons. The institutional SDOH-resource directory is curated and maintained.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every patient-education answer, every protocol-driven step, every care-plan reference is grounded in a cited source.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the bot is uncertain, when the patient's responses are ambiguous, when the conversation drifts toward clinical or operational judgment, the response defaults to "let me connect you with your care manager."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, attrition, task-completion, appointment-attendance, referral-completion, care-gap-closure, warm-handoff completion, and outcome metrics vary by language, channel, condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags, and program. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When any source system, any specialist bot, or any care-manager-workflow integration is unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble reaching part of your care information; let me connect you with your care team" with direct routing to the human care manager.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
